!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>. The poor monk died about eight more times during the CR process. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
That is sad, my alt is a monk, I've been on 4 naggy raids.  I ran one that was successful, been on 2 PU raids that were not, and the 4th I just happened to be in SolB anyhow, and CRed a failed raid.<br>
<br>
There is absolutely no reason to die CRing Naggy's room without a lot of really bad luck.<br>
<br>
Just run in, and FD.  Wait for FD to refresh, stand and run 2 steps, FD again, do this and you can literally FD'd under naggy, which I've done to get to the corpses that are behind him.<br>
<br>
Then you can summon all the corpses individually, the only problem is the 1-2 lame people that forgot to consent that you have to beg for it, and the 1-2 guys that went LD, left since the wipe.<br>
<br>
Once you have a pile on you, repeat backwards, stand move 2 steps, FD, make a new pile on you...<br>
<br>
I know, that is just way off on a tangent, just hate to hear of a monk dying so much. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Great job on your first raid, GL on any future attempts <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  .  That mask that drops off the Magus is pretty darn decent for a wizard too. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Edit:  Maybe someone else was agroing naggy... that could explain the first death... but not 8, as he should have told everyone else to get out of the room completely. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=delfontes>Delfontes</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.hartskeep.com/Shawn/deceit.jpg" BORDER=0> at: 4/22/03 9:50:11 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tsurok@graffeswizardcompilation>Tsurok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 74<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/22/03 10:36:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26210.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My First Naggy Raid!</span><hr size=1> After your first Naggy/Vox raid for the experience, I'd recommend not going on future pick-up raid unless the leader has secured a clicky stick and a few multi-group buffers.  Otherwise, buffing will take forever and, as a wizard, you'll take too much xp loss due to bind rushing.  I've seen a few higher levels on Bertoxx essentially sponsor a raid with MGBuffers. The buffers then get to roll on loot with the rest of the raid, if they wish, which seems fair to me,.<br>
<br>
IMO, since Vox and Naggy tend to be pick-up raids nowadays, I think they should scale back the dispell feature of their AE breath because no one 52 and under has MGB capability.  This means, for the level range these two dragons are intended, buffing is a royal PITA even for competent guilds, much less a pick up raid where it seems no one listens.  You shouldn't need MGB's for pick-up raids to be successful anymore for Naggy/Vox.  I'm sure others disagree.<br>
<br>
-Tsu<br>
52 Channeler<br>
<br>
PS-  I'm sure its was mentioned to you, but make sure you are under the Dragon when casting as you have to be in melee range for dd to hit.  IMO, being under the dragon isn't any better than anywhere else within melee range, but the dragons have a tendency to move/change targets during a fight (especially Naggy), so being underneath when you start  casting makes it more likely that you will remain in melee range when the spell finishes.  <br>
<br>
However, since DoF casts so quickly, I can just stand to the side of Vox and have never had any trouble landing spells. <br>
      <br>
